&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The East of England Ambulance Service is looking to appoint a Head of Organisational Development&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Postholder is responsible for ensuring that Organisational Development is embedded within the Trust, supporting the development and implementation &amp; standards of proficiency.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant masters level qualification or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organisational Development Practitioner qualification or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improvement methodology/approaches i.e. Lean, Six Sigma, PDSA, Model for Improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a key senior role in the Education and Training Team and will work as part of a team delivering high quality organisational development support to our existing staff, supporting them in their continued professional development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Watts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica.Watts@eastamb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
